On March 6, 2018, several nominations and appointments were sent to the Senate. James Edward Campos of Nevada was nominated to be the Director of the Office of Minority Economic Impact at the Department of Energy. He would replace LaDoris Guess Harris. Michael J. Desmond of California was nominated to be the Chief Counsel for the Internal Revenue Service and an Assistant General Counsel at the Department of the Treasury, replacing William J. Wilkins. Patrick Fuchs of Wisconsin was nominated to be a Member of the Surface Transportation Board for a term of five years. Jon Parrish Peede of Mississippi was nominated to be the Chairperson of the National Endowment for the Humanities for a term of four years, replacing William D. Adams. Lisa Porter of Virginia was nominated to be a Deputy Under Secretary of Defense, a new position. Michelle A. Schultz of Pennsylvania was nominated to be a Member of the Surface Transportation Board for a term of five years, also a new position. Finally, Peter C. Wright of Michigan was nominated to be the Assistant Administrator for the Office of Solid Waste at the Environmental Protection Agency, replacing Mathy Stanislaus.